  "title": "M&E Quantity Surveyor",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Description</strong></p><ul><li>Estimating, taking off the bill quantities and measuring the ACMV, Fire Protection, Plumbing and Sanitary and Electrical services from the tender drawings for commercial buildings and industrial building</li><li>Review all the tender drawings and specifications to understand the scope of work upon receiving the invitation from the main contractor, consultant, or clients.</li><li>Source for suppliers and request for quotation, and prepare price comparison and costing summary</li><li>Preparing all relevant administration and documentation for Tender submission, such as technical data, schedule of unit rate, catalogue submission.</li><li>Resource management, coordination with supplier and sub-contractors.</li><li>Work with project engineer to ensure compliance with contracts and monitoring of project costs.</li><li>Responsible of preparing progress payment claims, variation orders. project budgets & cost control, and settlement of the final account.</li></ul><p><br /></p><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>Diploma / Degree in Mechanical Engineering, Electrical Engineering or Building Services Engineering from a recognized University</li><li>4 years experience in the cost estimate, tendering, pre and post contract administration of either mechanical or electrical disciplines </li><li>Good interpersonal and teamwork skills</li><li>Good communication and written skills in English</li></ul><p><br /></p><p><strong>Suitable candidates are encouraged to apply this position via Apply Now button or email to Career@kah.com.sg</strong></p><p><em>Only shortlisted candidates will be notified.</em></p>",
